metadata.name: Sano #51
metadata.description:
Using Coronado’s algorithm as a starting point, Sano extends and embraces the notion of beauty existing in imperfection but allows for more impressionistic compositions with less structure, letting something atmospheric and understated emerge with subtle interactions that combine into dissonant chordal expressions infusing a breadth of emotion while maintaining a characteristic timbre.

Just as Coronado referenced a beat-up vintage guitar that had a patina and sound all its own, Sano refers to the vintage amp it was plugged into. A tube-amp from the 1960s with a spring reverb that when combined with single coils and hollow body of the guitar delivered screaming feedback as well as wonderfully gritty warm tones, which this algorithm attempts to echo visually.

There are 100 artist curated outputs in this short-form collection.

Keys:
S : save at current resolution
1 → 6 : save 2000x2500 → 12000x15000
(Chrome recommended for higher resolutions)

metadata.name: Dump of Links. Part II #91
metadata.description:
Audiovisual generative artwork. It continues with the proposal of the first part, revealing remote points of hills full of abandoned URLs, with a contemplative approach.

A ‘404 button’ shines from above, in the distance, as if it were a star that -possibly- watches over. And below, in a metaphor for pollution, rise islands of floating garbage. As if it were a calm, lonely, suffocating breath, and even sometimes dangerously attractive.

Original sound of voice, piano & synths.

[ s ] -> save 2160x2160px (in live view)
[ f ] -> fullscreen
[ q ] -> stop

Note: This artwork is an animated piece, and requires a powerful GPU for optimal real-time playback. It is important to note that it may not run properly on mobile devices, especially not high-end ones.

metadata.name: Asterium #288
metadata.description:
Asterium is a token that will grow with you, for an entire year. Changing and morphing over time to eventually reach its equilibrium.

It is a token where I try to symbolize the journey of life.
Where looking back is the best way to look forward.
Where looking into the future is not a possibility.
Where each day is as uncertain as the next.

A token that will surprise you and have its ups and downs as it grows over time.



Pricing:
Dutch auction 64-16-8, where anybody that picks one up at 64 tez gets a print of how their galaxy looks on any day from the present to day 0. Meaning you can claim the print at any point in the future.

The print will be printed on high quality hahnemühle torchon paper at 30x40 cm (11.81 x 15.75 in). Printed at a local print shop here in Utrecht. This paper has a rough texture to it that matches the textures of space perfectly.



Usage:
- Hover over your Asterium to view the name, date, days passed, status and render stats.
- Double press to export the current frame as a .png image.
- Use the slider at the bottom to scroll back in time to the days before today, you can go as far back as day 0 and as far forwards as today.
- The token refreshes every hour, so framing it in a digital picture frame is totally possible!
